7 An Act relating to Oklahoma Capitol Improvement
Authority; providing for allocation of funds from the
8 Legacy Capital Financing Fund; authorizing
utilization of certain amount for the purpose of
9 benefitting the Oklahoma State Bureau of
Investigation; requiring certain recapitalization
10 payments over certain period; authorizing certain
distributions; authorizing and limiting utilization
11 of memoranda of understanding; amending Section 1,
Chapter 391, O.S.L. 2024 (73 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
12 187A-11), which relates to the utilization of LCF
funds by the Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation;
13 designating certain facility; requiring certain
payments begin no later than certain condition; and
14 providing for codification.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 187A-15 of Title 73, unless
20 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 A. In addition to any other authorization provided by law, the
22 Oklahoma Capitol Improvement Authority is authorized to utilize
23 available funds from the Legacy Capital Financing Fund created by
24 Section 187B of Title 73 of the Oklahoma Statutes, in the amount of
ENGR. H. B. NO. 4056 Page 1

1 Twen ty-one Million Two Hundred Fifteen Thousand Dollars
2 ($21,215,000.00) for the benefit of the Oklahoma State Bureau of
3 Investigation to:
4 1. Construct, refurbish, or expand the Forensic Science Center;
5 and
6 2. Acquire, construct, or refurbish needed warehouse
7 facilities.
8 B. LCF Recapitalization Payments shall be made related to the
9 distribution of proceeds provided in subsection A of this section,
10 in accordance with the provisions of the Legacy Capital Financing
11 Act, provided that notwithstanding the provisions of subparagraph b
12 of paragraph 2 of subsection B of Section 187B of Title 73 of the
13 Oklahoma Statutes, such LCF Recapitalization Payments shall begin no
14 later than the month of May of the fiscal year in which subsection A
15 of this section becomes law.
16 C. The Authority may distribute funds authorized pursuant to
17 subsection A of this section in one or more tranches.
18 D. The Authority may enter memoranda of understanding with
19 agencies, departments, and subdivisions of the state as needed, to
20 facilitate the provisions of this act, provided that such memoranda
21 of understanding do not constitute a legal obligation of the State
22 of Oklahoma or impede the administration of the provisions of the
23 Legacy Capital Financing Act.
24
ENGR. H. B. NO. 4056 Page 2

1 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY Section 1, Chapter 391, O.S.L.
2 2024 (73 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 187A-11), is amended to read as
3 follows:
4 Section 187A-11. A. In addition to any other authorization
5 provided by law, the Oklahoma Capitol Improvement Authority is
6 authorized to utilize available funds from the Legacy Capital
7 Financing Fund created by Section 187B of Title 73 of the Oklahoma
8 Statutes this title, in the amount of Twenty-seven Million Five
9 Hundred Thousand Dollars ($27,500,000.00) for the benefit of the
10 Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation to construct, refurbish, or
11 expand the Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation headquarters and
12 related facilities, which shall be designated the Harvey Pratt
13 Building.
14 B. LCF Recapitalization Payments shall be made related to the
15 distribution of proceeds provided in subsection A of this section,
16 in accordance with the provisions of the Legacy Capital Financing
17 Act, provided that notwithstanding the provisions of subparagraph b
18 of paragraph 2 of subsection B of Section 187B of this title, such
19 LCF Recapitalization Payments shall begin no later than thirty (30)
20 days from the enactment of this act.
21 C. The Authority may distribute funds authorized pursuant to
22 subsection A of this section in one or more tranches.
23 D. The Authority may enter memoranda of understanding with
24 agencies, departments, and subdivisions of the state as needed, to
